    "# Day 3: Production Readiness - Hands-On Notebook\n",
    "\n",
    "Welcome to the Day 3 hands-on notebook! Today, we'll focus on making our agents robust and ready for the real world by implementing RAG, safety measures, and observability."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Activity 1: Building a RAG Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "We will build a simple Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system. This will allow our agent to answer questions based on a set of documents it wasn't trained on."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install openai-agents numpy scipy -q\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from openai import OpenAI\n",
    "from scipy.spatial.distance import cosine\n",
    "from agents import Agent, Runner, function_tool\n",
    "\n",
    "client = OpenAI()\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. Our Knowledge Base\n",
    "knowledge_base = {\n",
    "    "doc1": "The return policy for electronics is 14 days with a valid receipt.\",\n",
    "    "doc2": "For clothing, returns are accepted within 30 days, provided the items are unworn and have tags attached.\",\n",
    "    "doc3": "All sale items are final and cannot be returned or exchanged.\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Function to get embeddings\n",
    "def get_embedding(text, model=\"text-embedding-3-small\"):\n",
    "    return client.embeddings.create(input=[text], model=model).data[0].embedding\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3. Create embeddings for our knowledge base\n",
    "embedded_knowledge_base = {doc_id: get_embedding(text) for doc_id, text in knowledge_base.items()}\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Knowledge base embedded successfully!\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 4. Create the retrieval tool\n",
    "@function_tool\n",
    "def retrieve_policy_document(query: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"Retrieves the most relevant policy document for a user's query.\"\"\n",
    "    query_embedding = get_embedding(query)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Find the most similar document using cosine similarity\n",
    "    best_doc_id = min(embedded_knowledge_base.keys(), \n",
    "                      key=lambda doc_id: cosine(query_embedding, embedded_knowledge_base[doc_id]))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return knowledge_base[best_doc_id]\n",
    "\n",
    "# 5. Create a RAG Agent\n",
    "rag_agent = Agent(\n",
    "    name=\"Policy Q&A Agent\",\n",
    "    instructions=\"You are a customer service agent. When asked about a policy, use your retrieval tool to find the relevant document and then answer the user's question based on that document.\",\n",
    "    tools=[retrieve_policy_document]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "async def run_rag_agent():\n",
    "    result = await Runner.run(rag_agent, \"Can I return a shirt I bought on sale?\")\n",
    "    print(result.final_output)\n",
    "\n",
    "await run_rag_agent()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
